I"

<p><br /></p>

<h3 id="sr1-bfgs-dfp">SR1, BFGS, DFP</h3>

<ul>
  <li>SR1, BFGS, and DFP are all quasi-Newton methods that are commonly used for unconstrained optimization problems.</li>
  <li>all use an approximation of the Hessian matrix to compute a search direction for the optimization algorithm, but they differ in the way they construct and update the approximation.</li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h3 id="derivations-for-sr1-bfgs-dfp">Derivations for SR1, BFGS, DFP</h3>

